cff-version: 1.2.0
title: Flood Damage Prediction for the Kanto Region, Japan
message: >-
  If you use this software, please cite it and the underlying
  dataset (Wakai 2025, doi:10.5281/zenodo.14015790).
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Parth Krishan
    family-names: Goswami
    affiliation: Maharaja Surajmal Institute of Technology, GGSIPU
  - given-names: Aarushi
    family-names: Sen
    affiliation: Maharaja Surajmal Institute of Technology, GGSIPU
  - given-names: Soahum
    family-names: Trivedi
    affiliation: Maharaja Surajmal Institute of Technology, GGSIPU
  - given-names: Jyoti
    family-names: Arora
    affiliation: Maharaja Surajmal Institute of Technology, GGSIPU
repository-code: https://github.com/Parth-KG/Flood-Prediction
abstract: >-
  Comparison of five regression models - Random Forest, XGBoost, SVR,
  a deep neural network and linear regression - for predicting per-capita
  flood damage across 75 water systems in the Kanto region of Japan,
  1993-2020, using chronological and rolling-origin validation.
keywords:
  - flood damage prediction
  - machine learning
  - XGBoost
  - random forest
  - time series validation
  - Japan
license: MIT
